description.narrative: Strengthened national capacities, knowledge and resources to expand access to and completion of quality basic education for excluded and marginalised children (including transitions from pre-primary to primary to post-primary), with improved and relevant learning outcomes in development contexts and in emergency preparedness, response and recovery., which contributes to Equitable Access To Quality Education, Learning Outcomes, Skills Development, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Technical expertise and management support provided to all UNICEF work streams for the equitable achievement of the MDGs by 2015, realizing the rights of every child in humanitarian and development contexts
